('New Detachment Website!!!', 'Please use the new detachment website', '<p>Good Afternoon Cadets,</p><p><br></p><p>As many of you know I have been developing the new website for the detachment. I\'m happy to say it\'s just about finished (there will be a few more features added shortly). We will be shutting down the Word Press website so I wanted to let you know that as of today this will be new new official means of communication. </p><p>I wanted to point a few features out that will help make your lives easier below:</p><ol><li>The <a href=\"https://afrotc.union.rpi.edu/afrotc/directory.php\" target=\"_blank\">Cadet Directory</a>&nbsp;is where you can see each other\'s contact information.</li><li>The <a href=\"https://afrotc.union.rpi.edu/afrotc/announcements.php\" target=\"_blank\">Announcement Page</a>&nbsp;is where we will make announcements to the detachment. Once you click make announcement you will be able to select a group to notify. By default you will not notify any group however if you do select a group to be notified everyone in that group will be emailed a copy of the announcement.&nbsp;</li><li>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://afrotc.union.rpi.edu/afrotc/wikihome.php\" target=\"_blank\">Documentation Page</a>&nbsp;is where you can go with questions on how to use the site. This is an open forum (especially in the FAQ) section to put helpful information for your fellow cadets about website and ROTC related questions.</li><li>Finally, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://afrotc.union.rpi.edu/afrotc/sendemail.php\" target=\"_blank\">Send Email</a>&nbsp;page will be a place where you can utilize the detachment email to notify cadets about any upcoming PMT and Non PMT events and other important information ( do not abuse this ).&nbsp;</li></ol><p><br></p><p>Currently I believe I have enrolled everyone in the detachment on to the website however if I haven\'t please let me know and I\'ll add you asap. You can login to the website <a href=\"https://afrotc.union.rpi.edu/afrotc/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&nbsp;using your RIN and password (remember if you haven\'t changed your password your temporary password is 123123123).</p><p>I hope you enjoy the new site and please make me aware of any bugs you see while using it!</p><p><br></p><div style=\"caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\">--<br class=\"\">Very Respectfully,<br class=\"\"><br class=\"\">JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/1st Lt,&nbsp;AFROTC<br class=\"\">Deputy Commander, Alpha Flight<br class=\"\">550th Training Squadron</div><div style=\"caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><a href=\"mailto:messaj@rpi.edu\" class=\"\">messaj@rpi.edu</a></div><div style=\"caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\">(585) 500-9728</div>', 661550966, 14, '2018-12-08 18:53:29'),
('LLAB 14', 'Operation: Change of Command', '<p>Cadets,&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Operation: Change of Command Parade/End of Semester Feedback Session</p><p>Date: 12 December 2018</p><p>Location: Armory Floor&nbsp;</p><p>Time: POC: 0740</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;GMC: 0750</p><p><span style=\"caret-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-size-adjust: auto;\">UOD: The Uniform of the Day (UOD) will be Service Dress</span><span style=\"caret-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-size-adjust: auto;\">.&nbsp; Cadets who have not been issued Service Dress</span><span style=\"caret-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>will wear Black Polo and Khakis (BPAK</span><span style=\"caret-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-size-adjust: auto;\">).</span></p><p><span style=\"caret-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"caret-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-size-adjust: auto;\">Very Respectfully,</span></p><p class=\"p1\">SYDNEY E.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>LUKE, C/3C, AFROTC</p><p class=\"p1\">Materiel Flight</p><p class=\"p1\">550th AFROTC Force Support Squadron<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p1\">lukes@rpi.edu</p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<style type=\"text/css\">\r\np.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px \'Helvetica Neue\'; color: #454545}\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"p1\">(518) 729-9887</p>', 661582760, 15, '2018-12-12 01:28:43'),
('New Feature', 'Login with your email', '<p>Cadets,&nbsp;</p><p>Per your request I have updated the new website so that you can log in with your account\'s primary email. This will work as long as you have added your email to your account already.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>--</p><p>Very Respectfully,</p><p><br></p><p>JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/1st Lt, AFROTC</p><p>Deputy Commander, Alpha Flight</p><p>550th Training Squadron</p><p>messaj@rpi.edu</p><p><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 1rem;\">(585) 500-9728</span></p>', 661550966, 16, '2018-12-12 02:08:26'),
('Majors Added', 'School Major Function Added to Profiles', '<p>Good Morning Cadets,</p><p>I have added two new functions to the website. The first is the ability to add your major to your profile so if you now go in and look at your profile you will see a major section that is blank. Please fill this out when you get the time because it will allow the other feature to be useful. The second feature I added was the ability to search for cadets on the directory page based off of their major. That drop down will show all of the cadets with the same major as you (please spell out your majors completely because if they don\'t match exactly right now you won\'t be considered in the same major). As always let me know if you find bugs or issues with this.</p><p><br></p><p>--</p><p>Very Respectfully,</p><p><br></p><p>JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/1st Lt, AFROTC</p><p>Deputy Commander, Alpha Flight</p><p>550th Training Squadron</p><p>messaj@rpi.edu</p><p>(585) 500-9728</p>', 661550966, 17, '2018-12-14 13:17:09'),
('New GroupMe Integration', 'GroupMe', '<p><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Good Afternoon Cadets,</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">I wanted to make everyone aware of a new feature that is now live on the new detachment website. You should see this anouncement on you GroupMe as well as through email and finally on the site. This will ensure no one misses a post or any informaiton that may pertain to them. As always if you find a bug please notify someone in ECPA flight so we can address it.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">--</span><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Very Respectfully,</span><br class=\"\" /><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/1st Lt,&nbsp;AFROTC</span><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Deputy Commander, Alpha Flight</span><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">550th Training Squadron</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"\" href=\"mailto:messaj@rpi.edu\">messaj@rpi.edu</a></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">(585) 500-9728</span></div>', 661550966, 22, '2019-01-22 17:42:08'),
('Master Attendance', 'New Master Attendance Feature', '<p><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Good Afternoon Cadets,</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">I have created a new feature called master attendance that you will now see on the website with your name and each event that has happened so far this semester. You will see either \"P\" for present, \"A\" for absent, or \"E\" for excused. This will enable you to see your current attendance status in the det at all times. If you have disputes with your attendance please take it up with your chain of command. The totals on the right will not account for whether or not you\'re on the cross town program or have had the event waived. If that is the case do not worry about it for right now. In the future it will get set as excused however that is not set up currently.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">--</span><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Very Respectfully,</span><br class=\"\" /><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/1st Lt,&nbsp;AFROTC</span><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Deputy Commander, Alpha Flight</span><br class=\"\" /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">550th Training Squadron</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"\" href=\"mailto:messaj@rpi.edu\">messaj@rpi.edu</a></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">(585) 500-9728</span></div>', 661550966, 23, '2019-01-25 19:36:28'),
('LLAB 2 Survey', 'LLAB 2 Survey', '<p>Cadets,<br /><br />Below is a survey for LLAB 2 (Jan 29). Please fill it out before COB Thursday.<br />Fill out THIS survey.<br /><br />--<br />Very Respectfully,<br /><br />PHU T. THAI, C/4C, AFROTC<br />Standardization and Evaluation Flight<br />550th AFROTC Training Support Squadron<br />thaip@rpi.edu<br />(315) 420-7868</p>', 661965691, 24, '2019-01-29 18:32:18'),
('Official Switch to New Website', 'Website', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We will now be officially switching over to the new website. You should receive an email at 2100 and message notification on GroupMe about this post (if not please contact a member of ECPA Flight ASAP).&nbsp;Please take a minute to further familiarize yourself with the website, look at the <em>Website Standardization</em> page under Documentation, and update your profile as specified (link GroupMe as well).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, concerns, bugs, or recommendations do not hesitate to contact a member of ECPA Flight.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>KATHERINE G. DONOVAN, C/3C, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Education, Communications, and Public Affairs Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Communications Squadron&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>donovk5@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(847) 682-0262</p>', 661788027, 25, '2019-01-29 18:51:04'),
